com.vectorprint.configuration

Class Settings

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<String,String[]>
        • com.vectorprint.configuration.Settings
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EnhancedMap, Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,String[]>

    public final class Settings
extends HashMap<String,String[]>
implements EnhancedMap
    Enhances Java Map with support for data types, debugging info, working with default values in code. You cannot subclass this class, instead subclass AbstractPropertiesDecorator and wrap an instance of this class.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth at VectorPrint.nl
    See Also:
    EnhancedMapBindingFactory, com.vectorprint.configuration.decoration, SettingsAnnotationProcessor, SettingsField, Setting, Serialized Form

      • addDecorator

        public void addDecorator(Class<? extends AbstractPropertiesDecorator> clazz)
        Called by AbstractPropertiesDecorator.AbstractPropertiesDecorator(com.vectorprint.configuration.EnhancedMap) to build a list of wrappers for these settings. When wrapped your code should call methods on the outermost wrapper only, if you don't, functionality of wrappers will not be called. The preferred way to achieve this is to use the SettingsField annotation in conjunction with a call to SettingsAnnotationProcessor.initSettings(java.lang.Object, com.vectorprint.configuration.EnhancedMap) }.
        Parameters:
        clazz -
